column5: That there is what we like to refer to as a "bench".
Well it must be, it definately isn't a "perch".
Not a Muskoka chair, must be a Bama bench seat.
Facinating fin pattern Clamp-It  best guess--a Floridian Tourist Trap Bench with the head cushion removed--its proximity to the discounted clothes rack was my first clue..lol!  Paul
I would say it's a pumpkinseed motif, country crappie log settee
I concour with the shirt-less wonder from down yonder.  "red-eared sunfish" bench, also known as the shellcraker, 'cause they luv them snails.   (hmmn, must be french then)  reefrunner
I've been called worse!  ... just don't call me late for the Biscuits and Gravy!!!
Didn't mean to offend GCD.  As you can see from the pics in my intro, I too have the same "less is more" attitude when it comes to fishing fashion.  reefrunner
There there my friend is a Buttomus gargantuios
~~~I'm a thunken that Lex has it nailed
No offence taken RR, I was just kiddin' around too!
